<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-02-02T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-02-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="186" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d186">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2844: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at
                                Geneva</hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-02-02T18:00:00-05:00">February 2, 1933—6
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>62. Your 90, Feb. 2, 4 p.m. Department did not take up matter with
                            Neutral Commission. However, Department knows from past experience and
                            from recent casual conversations with members of Neutral Commission that
                            they all share its views in the matter. However, Commission as such was
                            not consulted.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>